home__feedback\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:373:      {loadState === 'ready' && totalSessions === 0 ? (\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:374:        <EmptySessionsState />\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:376:      {loadState === 'ready' && totalSessions > 0 ? (\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:379:          className=\"sessions-panel\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:381:          title=\"Recent sessions\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:384:            <SessionGroup\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:385:              description=\"Drafts, active workflows, and sessions that need a refreshed output.\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:386:              sessions={active}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:392:            <SessionGroup\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:394:              sessions={completed}\ndocs/README.md:9:- `domain-model.md`: durable session entities, workflow-stage contract, and stage-state rules\ndocs/README.md:15:- `realtime-events.md`: session-channel contract, live event families, replay rules, and local auth assumptions\ndocs/README.md:16:- `realtime-events.schema.json`: machine-readable schema bundle for subscription frames and session events\ndocs/product-brief.md:5:Storyteller is a session-based bedtime story creation studio. It helps a user move from a loose story idea to a finished written story and finished narration audio, with the ability to leave and come back later without losing progress.\ndocs/product-brief.md:7:The first meaningful screen is the sessions home. It must foreground past sessions, including both in-progress and completed stories, so resume and revisit are the default behaviors rather than an afterthought.\ndocs/product-brief.md:12:- Guided, not opaque: users move through explicit workflow stages instead of one giant prompt box.\ndocs/product-brief.md:24:4. Story pitches generated by Gemini, with selection, refinement, or regeneration.\ndocs/product-brief.md:25:5. Character sheet generation, again with selection and refinement.\ndocs/product-brief.md:26:6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet generation and editing.\ndocs/product-brief.md:34:### Sessions and Resume\ndocs/product-brief.md:36:- Sessions are durable backend entities.\ndocs/product-brief.md:37:- A user can reopen a session from any stage.\ndocs/product-brief.md:38:- In-progress and completed sessions both appear on the home screen.\ndocs/product-brief.md:49:- The model may propose actions, but a deterministic backend policy layer decides whether each action is valid for the session's current stage.\ndocs/product-brief.md:84:- resume work from prior sessions without losing context\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:7:const sampleSessions = [\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:70:function mockSessionsApi({\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:71:  postSessionId = 'new-session',\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:72:  sessions = sampleSessions,\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:75:  postSessionId?: string\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:76:  sessions?: ReadonlyArray<Record<string, unknown>>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:84:      if (url.endsWith('/api/v1/sessions') && init?.method === 'POST') {\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:85:        return Promise.resolve(buildJsonResponse(201, { id: postSessionId }))\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:88:      if (url.includes('/api/v1/sessions?limit=20')) {\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:89:        return Promise.resolve(buildJsonResponse(status, sessions))\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:103:  it('renders active and completed sessions from the backend', async () => {\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:104:    mockSessionsApi()\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:123:    ).toHaveAttribute('href', '/sessions/juniper-lake')\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:128:    ).toHaveAttribute('href', '/sessions/maple-hollow'