:9:- Every event belongs to exactly one `story_session`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:10:- Events are append-only and ordered by a per-session `sequence_number`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:22:The backend centralizes these names in `backend/app/models/events.py` as `SessionEventType`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:27:| `session.created` | Root audit entry for a new session. | `user` | none |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:29:| `selection.recorded` | Accepted or candidate selection for genre, tone, pitch, character sheet, beat sheet, or story setup. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:30:| `ai.output.recorded` | AI-generated batch or revision that the session may later accept or refine. | `assistant` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:57:  \"invalidated_stages\": [\"pitches\", \"characters\", \"beats\", \"composition\", \"audio\", \"finalize\"],\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:58:  \"current_stage\": \"pitches\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:59:  \"resume_stage\": \"pitches\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:75:  \"summary_text\": \"Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.\"\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:80:`SessionEventLogService.append_event(...)` still injects `schema_version: 1`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:89:- `record_session_created(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:99:- `list_session_history(...)` for timeline reads\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:102:`backend/app/repositories/events.py`. It is responsible for per-session sequencing and\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:112:from app.services.event_log import SessionEventLogService\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:114:event_log = SessionEventLogService(db_session)\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:116:    session_id,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:129:    session_id,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:141:history = event_log.list_session_history(session_id, after_sequence_number=10)\nfrontend/README.md:10:- `src/app/router.tsx`: browser-router configuration for the home page, session workspace, and not-found fallback\nfrontend/README.md:12:- `src/app/routePaths.ts`: central path helpers, including the session-workspace URL builder\nfrontend/README.md:19:- `src/features/session/sessionQueries.ts`: React Query hooks and cache keys for session server state\nfrontend/README.md:20:- `src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts`: local session runtime store for live events and optimistic actions\nfrontend/README.md:28:- `src/features/`: reusable product-domain logic that can be shared across pages, including session query hooks and runtime state\nfrontend/README.md:32:- `src/state/`: state models and future global/session store modules\nfrontend/README.md:44:Later prompts should extend this TypeScript app into the sessions-first workspace rather than replacing it.\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:8:from app.db.session import get_engine, get_session_factory\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:10:from app.services import SessionService\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:25:    get_session_factory.cache_clear()\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:35:    get_session_factory.cache_clear()\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:41:    db_session = get_session_factory()()\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:54:        db_session.add_all([genre, tone])\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:55:        db_session.flush()\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:56:        session_id = SessionService(db_session).create_session(working_title=\"Lantern Cove\").id\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:57:        db_session.commit()\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:59:        db_session.close()\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:62:        f\"/api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/actions/evaluate\",\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:84:    assert payload[\"session_id\"] == session_id\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:92:def test_evaluate_actions_endpoint_returns_404_for_missing_session(\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_api.py:96:        \"/api/v1/sessions/missing-session/actions/evaluate\",\nbackend/tests/test_action_