and echo that action into session history.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:27:      'pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:28:      'characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:39:      'Choose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:50:      'pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:51:      'characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:72:      'pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:73:      'characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:81:    id: 'pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:82:    label: 'Pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:85:    scaffoldTitle: 'Review and select story pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:87:      'Pitch generation will give the user multiple bedtime-suitable directions before the session commits to a single story lane.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:89:      'Display multiple candidate pitch cards from the planner model.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:91:      'Persist the accepted pitch as the story lane for characters and beats.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:94:      'characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:102:    id: 'characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:103:    label: 'Characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:105:      'Define the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:106:    scaffoldTitle: 'Shape the character sheet',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:108:      'The character stage will turn the accepted pitch into a durable cast sheet that later planning and writing can trust.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:110:      'Present character-sheet candidates with bedtime-fit notes and traits.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:118:    label: 'Beat sheet',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:119:    description: 'Store the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts:122:      'This panel will hold the explicit beat sheet so the bedtime arc stays structured, editable, and easy to revisit.',\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:8:Storyteller is a session-based bedtime story studio, not a single-shot prompt demo. A user needs to move through a staged workflow, leave, come back later, and still see the current plan, generated text, generated audio, and recent activity.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:13:- session state needs to survive refreshes, restarts, and long-running work\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:29:- The backend policy layer decides whether a model-suggested action is valid for the current workflow stage before state changes are accepted.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:33:PostgreSQL owns the structured state required to resume a story session.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:37:- session\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:38:- workflow stage\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:41:- brief, pitch batch, selected pitch\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:42:- character sheet candidates and selection\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:43:- beat sheet\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:49:Session resume should come from durable state, not browser cache. The event history is part of the product, not just an internal log, because it supports replay, auditability, and UI-to-chat echoes.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:66:- WebSockets handle session progress, job status, and incremental event delivery.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:67:- On reconnect, the client should rehydrate from durable session state and recent event history before continuing with live updates.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:69:The websocket channel is a delivery mechanism, not the source of truth. If a socket drops, the session must still be recoverable from PostgreSQL and storage.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:85:- They guide pitch generation, beat planning, and composition prompts.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:110:- Treat the durable event history as product data that can be queried during session resume.\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:2:import type { SessionSnapshot } from '../../../api/sessions.ts'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:4:  buildSessionChatQuickActions,\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:5:  buildSessionChatQuickActionSubmission,\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:6:  buildSessionChatSlashCommandHint,\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:7:  resolveSessionChatSlashCommand,\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:10:const sampleSnapshot: SessionSnapshot = {\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:16:  furthest_completed_stage: 'characters',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:39:  selected_pitch: {\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:40:    id: 'pitch-1',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:42:    pitch_index: 0,\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:46:  selected_character_sheet: null,\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:63:    const quickActions = buildSessionChatQuickActions({\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:75:        commandId: 'regenerate_pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:76:        label: 'Regenerate pitches',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.test.ts:77:        slashCommand: '/rege