\nQA Character Stage\n\nChat and stage-driven workflow controls now share one persistent surface, with the left lane reserved for conversation and the right canvas reserved for structured editing.\n\nCurrent stage\nBeat sheet\nSave status\nSaved Apr 2, 5:41 AM\nSession ID\n71281140-6108-4b8f-a1d1-f26c5ebeb4b4\nLive updates\nIdle\n\nSet VITE_SESSION_EVENTS_WS_URL to enable live updates.\n\nIn progress\nReturn home\nLive feed idle\nIn progress\n\nThe workspace is running from the durable snapshot only. Configure the websocket endpoint to start session-scoped live updates.\n\nChat lane\n\nMessages, action echoes, and redirect notes stay visible beside the structured workflow.\n\nLive feed idle\n\nReady for notes, approvals, and stage edits from the conversation lane.\n\nSystem\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSession opened. Resume at Beat sheet.\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSelected genre: Quest Fantasy\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSelected tone: Hushed Wonder\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSaved story brief from workspace.\n\nAssistant\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nGenerated 3 pitch options. Generated pitches: The Mapped Lanterns Promise, The Quiet Docks Question, The Silver Water Map.\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSelected pitch: The Mapped Lanterns Promise\n\nAssistant\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nGenerated 3 character sheets. Generated character sheets: Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast, Quiet Docks Listener Cast, Silver Water Guide Cast.\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSelected character sheet: Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast\n\nAssistant\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nGenerated 1 character sheets. Generated refined character sheet Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast: Revised from Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast.\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSelected character sheet: Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast: Revised\n\nMessage composer\n\nSend approvals, nudges, or revision notes without leaving the current workspace stage.\n\nReady\nQuick actions\n\nRun a common action in one tap, or type the slash version.\n\nCommands\nNext stage\nRegenerate pitches\nSummarize plan\n\nSlash commands: /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan\n\nMessage composer\n\nPress Enter to send. Press Shift+Enter for a new line. Try /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan.\n\n0/1200 characters\n\nSend message\nWorkflow canvas\n\nThe main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and later composition or audio progress views.\n\nQueued\nStage navigator\n\nEvery required workflow step is visible now, with URL-backed panel selection that can coexist with backend-owned stage truth.\n\n01\n\nSTAGE 01\n\nGenre\n\nChoose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n02\n\nSTAGE 02\n\nTone\n\nChoose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nShape the character sheet\n\nThe character stage will turn the accepted pitch into a durable cast sheet that later planning and writing can trust.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\n\nThe route is previewing characters via the stage query parameter while the durable session state remains at beat sheet.\n\nCurrent selection\n\nMapped Lanterns Keeper Cast: Revised\n\nRefined from \"Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast\" with: Make the support cast siblings who settle together after the last harbor errand..\n\nLatest batch\n\nRefined cast ready\n\nRefined from Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast. Make the support cast siblings who settle together after the last harbor errand.\n\ncharacter-batch-4accee88e61a\nRefinement\n\nNext step\n\nBeat sheet is ready next\n\nBeat generation can now stay anchored to the accepted cast and relationship dynamics.\n\nPreview beat stage\nNew character batches refresh downstream work\n\nGenerating a new batch reopens character review and refreshes later planning. The currently accepted sheet stays visible while you compare new cast options.\n\nGenerate a character batch\n\nCreate several cast directions from the accepted pitch, then compare them as durable cards before beats are generated.\n\nReady to compare\nCharacter sheet count\n3 candidates\n4 candidates\n5 candidates\nOptional character guidance\n\nOptional guidance can steer the next cast batch. For example: make the lead more cautious, add a sibling dynamic, or keep the support cast smaller.\n\nRegenerate character sheets\nRevisit pitches\nRefine a saved character sheet\n\nPick one saved cast, describe the change, and save the refined result as a new durable option without losing earlier sheets.\n\nReady to refine\nCharacter sheet to refine\nRev 04 \u00b7 Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast: Revised\nRev 01 \u00b7 Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast\nRev 02 \u00b7 Quiet Docks Listener Cast\nRev 03 \u00b7 Silver Water Guide Cast\nRefinement instructions\n\nDescribe the specific cast change to apply. For example: give the lead a quieter flaw, make the support cast siblings, or add a more obvious comfort ritual.\n\nRefine character sheet\nMapped Lanterns Keeper Cast: Revised\nLatest character batch\n\nThe newest batch stays first so the strongest cast options are quick to compare. Earlier batches remain below for resume and review.\n\nGenerated Apr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nSHEET 01\n\nMapped Lanterns Keeper Cast: Revised\n\nThis revision keeps Mapped Lanterns Keeper Cast recognizable while applying: Make the support cast siblings who settle together after the last harbor errand..\n\ncharacter-batch-4accee88e61a\nRefined\nSelected\n\nLead signal. sleepy lantern-keeper in training Goal: guide the last mapped lanterns home before a moonlit harbor can rest Flaw: tries to solve every worry alone before asking for help Comfort trait: counts steady lights until their breathing slows down\n\nSupporting cast. Otis (revised steadying companion) - Works in closer sync with Mira after the revision. Lark (revised supporting mirror) - Reflects Mira's growth in a lighter key.\n\nBedtime notes. The revision keeps all emotional pressure buffered by companionship, clear naming, and a visibly safe return to calm.\n\nSelected sheet\nEarlier character batches\n\nOlder generations stay available so the user can revisit prior cast directions instead of losing them after each refresh.\n\n1 earlier batch\n\nEarlier batch\n\n3 saved options\n\nGenerated Apr 2, 5:41 AM\n\nMapped Lanterns Keeper Cast\nQuiet Docks Listener Cast\nSilver Water Guide Cast\n\nProgress\n\nWorkflow progress\n5 of 10 stages complete\n\nResume at Beat sheet with 50% of the workflow currently complete.\n\nStory lane\n\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\n\nA sleepy apprentice agrees to carry mapped lanterns across a moonlit harbor so the whole night can settle into place.\n\nProduction\n\nBeat sheet\n\nComposition and audio controls will take over this area once the planning stages are complete.\n    at assertText (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:66:11)\n    at async runStep (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:137:7)\n    at async main (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:224:7)\n\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml -f .artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-46-compose.override.yml run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-46-character-stage-desktop.spec.json'", "exit_code": 1, "id": "item_251", "status": "failed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 517, "prompt_index": 47, "prompt_name": "46 \u2014 Character Sheet Generation Pipeline", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T22:42:36-07:00"}
